#. [part]
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\01_Another_Patrol.cfg:85
msgid ""
"This campaign is designed to also work without the War of Legends add-on.\n"
"            \n"
"War of Legends is currently installed which means you will play the version "
"with vampire units from the Era of Myths.\n"
"\n"
"If you want to play the other (lesser) version, uninstall the War of Legends "
"add-on.\n"
"\n"
"Do note, the other version is meant as a 'stopgap' for people who cannot "
"install War of Legends for some reason.\n"
"\n"
"In any case, onto the story!"
msgstr ""
"Cette campagne est aussi conçue pour fonctionner sans l'extension War of "
"Legends.\n"
"\n"
"Celle-ci est présentement installée donc la campagne se déroulera avec des "
"unités vampires de l'Era of Myths.\n"
"\n"
"Si tu préfères jouer à l'autre version (inférieure), il suffit de "
"désinstaller l'extension War of Legends.\n"
"\n"
"Note: L'autre version a pour but d'être une solution de rechange pour "
"quiconque ne peut pas installer War of Legends.\n"
"\n"
"Dans tous les cas, en avant vers l'histoire!"

#. [part]
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\01_Another_Patrol.cfg:100
msgid ""
"This campaign is designed to also work without the <i>War of Legends</i> add-"
"on.\n"
"            \n"
"It is currently not installed which means you will play the version without "
"vampire units from the Era of Myths.\n"
"\n"
"If you want to play the other (better) version, install the <i>War of "
"Legends</i> add-on.\n"
"\n"
"Do note, this version is meant as a 'stopgap' for people who cannot install "
"War of Legends for some reason.\n"
"\n"
"In any case, onto the story!"
msgstr ""
"Cette campagne est aussi conçue pour fonctionner sans l'extension <i>War of "
"Legends</i>.\n"
"\n"
"Celle-ci n'est présentement pas installée donc la campagne se déroulera sans "
"les unités vampires de l'Era of Myths.\n"
"\n"
"Si tu préfères jouer à l'autre version (supérieure), il suffit d'installer "
"l'extension <i>War of Legends</i>.\n"
"\n"
"Note: Cette version a pour but d'être une solution de rechange pour "
"quiconque ne peut pas installer War of Legends.\n"
"\n"
"\n"
"Dans tous les cas, en avant vers l'histoire!"

#. [part]
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\01_Another_Patrol.cfg:115
msgid ""
"In the year 253 since the founding of Wesnoth, the kingdom prospered under "
"the rule of Haldric III, King of Wesnoth.\n"
"\n"
"The orcish menace had been beaten back and the lands between Elensefar and "
"Weldyn pacified."
msgstr ""
"En l'an 253 depuis la fondation de Wesnoth, le royaume prospérait sous le "
"règne de Haldric III, Roi de Wesnoth. \n"
"\n"
"La menace orc avait été repoussée et les terres entre Elensefar et Weldyn "
"pacifiées."

#. [part]
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\01_Another_Patrol.cfg:120
msgid ""
"Since 199YW, colonization of the lands north of the Great River had begun "
"and now, more than fifty years later, thriving settlements had sprung up at "
"the foot of the Heart Mountains and even beyond, in the Far North."
msgstr ""
"Depuis 199YW, la colonisation des terres au nord du Grand Fleuve avaient "
"commencées et maintenant, plus de cinquante ans après, des patelins "
"prospères avaient vu jour au pied des Montagnes Centrales, et même plus "
"loin, dans le Grand Nord."

#. [part]
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\01_Another_Patrol.cfg:123
msgid ""
"However, while the rest of the kingdom enjoyed relative peace, this was far "
"from the case in the northernmost reaches where the orcish presence was far "
"greater than further south.\n"
"            \n"
"This, in turn, led to widespread banditry as the army was often occupied "
"repelling orcish incursions."
msgstr ""
"Cependant, bien que le reste du royaume était relativement paisible, c'était "
"loin d'être le cas dans les régions nordiques où la présence orc était bien "
"plus importante que plus au sud.\n"
"\n"
"Ceci menait à du banditisme répandu comme l'armée était souvent occupée par "
"des incursions orcs à repousser."

#. [part]
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\01_Another_Patrol.cfg:128
msgid ""
"The early settlements would not have survived without help from knightly "
"orders who roamed the land, safeguarding vital trade routes and protecting "
"the citizenry from ne'er-do-wells.\n"
"\n"
"Amongst these righteous bands of warriors there were the Knights of the "
"Silver Spire, named for the argent shine of the tower that served as their "
"headquarters within Dorest, the largest city north of the Longlier."
msgstr ""
"Les premières colonies n'auraient pas survécu sans l'aide d'ordre de "
"chevaliers qui parcouraient le royaume, défendant des routes commerciales "
"vitales et protégeant le peuple contre des bons à riens.\n"
"\n"
"Parmi ces bandes de guerriers virtueux se trouvaient els chevaliers de la "
"Tour d'Argent, nommés ainsi pour la couleur argentée de la tour qui leur "
"servait de quartier général dans Dorest, la plus grande ville au nord de la "
"rivière Long-Repos."

#. [part]
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\01_Another_Patrol.cfg:133
msgid ""
"Their leader was a young knight of the realm who had gone alongside his "
"friends to help make the Northlands safe.\n"
"            \n"
"Though they were relatively new and few in numbers, they had already started "
"to establish themselves as stalwart defenders of the innocent and were "
"tireless in their battles against the enemies of the kingdom."
msgstr ""
"Leur meneur était un jeune chevalier du royaume qui était allé avec ses amis "
"aider à rendre le nord sûr.\n"
"\n"
"Bien qu'ils étaient relativement nouveaux et peu nombreux, ils avaient déjà "
"commencé à s'établir comme de vaillants protecteurs des innocents et étaient "
"infatigables dans leurs combats contre les ennemis du royaume."

#. [part]
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\01_Another_Patrol.cfg:140
msgid ""
"It was thus just another day, another patrol on the road towards Lmarig when "
"they learned that the village was being raided by bandits, servants of the "
"Crimson Duke, a new bandit lord that had risen in the region.\n"
"\n"
"They sped with all haste towards the village, hoping to help the villagers "
"and perhaps even find some way to take out the bandits' leader."
msgstr ""
"Ceci n'était donc une journée comme les autres, une autre patrouille sur la "
"route vers Lmarig lorsqu'ils apprirent que le village était en train d'être "
"mis à sac par des bandits, des servants du Duc Pourpre, un nouveau seigneur "
"bandit qui était apparu dans la région.\n"
"\n"
"Ils se dirigèrent en toute hâte vers le village, espérant aider les "
"villageois et peut-être même découvrir une manière de vaincre le chef de ces "
"bandits."

#. [part]
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\01_Another_Patrol.cfg:145
msgid ""
"Chapter One\n"
"<i>Just Another Patrol</i>"
msgstr ""
"Chapitre Un\n"
"<i>Juste une autre patrouille</i>"

#. [message]: speaker=BL1
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\01_Another_Patrol.cfg:164
msgid ""
"Oh my, ya didn't have that many riches but hey, it's still sum'thing. Tha "
"Crimson Duke'll be happy!"
msgstr ""
"Oh là là, vous 'viez pas beaucoup de choses mais bon, c'est quelq'chose. Le "
"Duc Pourpre sera ben content!"

#. [message]: speaker=MC
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\01_Another_Patrol.cfg:168
msgid "You pitiful wretch, attacking defenseless civilians!"
msgstr "Sale vermine qui ose attaquer des villageois sans défense!"

#. [message]: speaker=BL1
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\01_Another_Patrol.cfg:172
msgid ""
"Foolish knights, prancing around... Aight boys, pack up the stuff, we're "
"leavin' with da loot!"
msgstr ""
"Que de naïfs chevaliers, sautillant partout… Bon les gars, ramassez le "
"butin, on s'en va avec!"

#. [message]: speaker=MC
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\01_Another_Patrol.cfg:176
msgid ""
"Rabble like you should be hanging, not blabbering. Let us rectify this "
"travesty forthwith."
msgstr ""
"La canaille comme vous devrait pendre, pas se vanter. Nous allons rectifier "
"cette travestie dans les plus brefs délais."

#. [message]: speaker=BL1
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\01_Another_Patrol.cfg:188
msgid "Fall back, fall ba—!"
msgstr "Retraite, retrai—!"

#. [message]: speaker=second_unit
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\01_Another_Patrol.cfg:198
msgid "The scum is dead."
msgstr "La racaille est morte."

#. [message]: speaker=MC
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\01_Another_Patrol.cfg:205
msgid ""
"Scatter the wretches. They will run back to their main camp and we will "
"slaughter them there."
msgstr ""
"Dispersez ces vermines. Ils fuiront vers le camp principal et nous les "
"massacrerons là-bas."

#. [message]: speaker=BL1
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\01_Another_Patrol.cfg:214
msgid "We've got all we could've asked for. Let's lose'em in the mountains!"
msgstr ""
"On a tout ce qu'on aurait pu vouloir. On perdra les chevaliers dans les "
"montagnes!"

#. [message]: speaker=MC
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\01_Another_Patrol.cfg:218
msgid "No! The villagers won't survive without food!"
msgstr "Non! Les villageois ne survivront pas sans nourriture!"

#. [scenario]: id=02_Bandit_Camp
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\02_Bandit_Camp.cfg:5
msgid "Bandit Camp"
msgstr "Le camp des bandits"

#. [part]
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\02_Bandit_Camp.cfg:71
msgid ""
"After the battle, the remains of the bandit force dispersed, trying to head "
"back to safety and their camp.\n"
"\n"
"The knights followed them into the mountains, that they might put an end to "
"this specific threat, once and for all."
msgstr ""
"Après la bataille, les restes de la troupe de bandits se dispersa, les "
"survivants essayant désespérément de retourner à leur camp et d'y être en "
"sûreté.\n"
"\n"
"Les chevaliers les suivirent dans les montagnes pour mettre fin à cette "
"menace une fois pour toute."

#. [part]
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\02_Bandit_Camp.cfg:76
msgid ""
"Chapter Two\n"
"<i>Bandit Camp</i>"
msgstr ""
"Chapitre Deux\n"
"<Le camp des bandits</i>"

#. [message]: speaker=MC
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\02_Bandit_Camp.cfg:95
msgid "Oh my, more vermin to kill..."
msgstr "O là là, plus de racaille à tuer..."

#. [message]: speaker=BBM
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\02_Bandit_Camp.cfg:99
msgid "Fools, you led them right here!"
msgstr "Crétins, vous les avez menés ici!"

#. [message]: speaker=BL1
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\02_Bandit_Camp.cfg:103
msgid "I'll handle 'em master, the Crimson Duke won't be unhappy!"
msgstr "J' m'occupe d'eux maître, le Duc Pourpre ne s'ra pas mécontent!"

#. [message]: speaker=BBM
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\02_Bandit_Camp.cfg:107
msgid "See that you give him no cause to be displeased."
msgstr "Voyez à ne pas lui donner de raison d'être contrarié."

#. [message]: speaker=MC
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\02_Bandit_Camp.cfg:120
msgid ""
"That man seemed to be their leader. We must go through them fast and catch "
"him!"
msgstr ""
"Cet homme semblait être leur meneur. Nous devons en finir rapidement avec "
"eux pour le capturer!"

#. [message]: speaker=BL1
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\02_Bandit_Camp.cfg:132
msgid "Nooo, master!"
msgstr "Nooon, maître!"

#. [message]: speaker=second_unit
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\02_Bandit_Camp.cfg:142
msgid ""
"And down he goes... That amount of devotion was unusual, however... Is it "
"because of that <i>Crimson Duke</i> they have as a leader?"
msgstr ""
"Et le voilà qui tombe au combat... Cette dévotion était inhabituelle pour un "
"bandit par contre… Est-ce à cause de ce <i>Duc Pourpre</i> qu'ils ont comme "
"chef?"

#. [message]: speaker=MC
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\02_Bandit_Camp.cfg:149
msgid "Let us try and catch their <i>master</i> to find out why."
msgstr "Essayons d'attraper leur <i>maître</i> pour comprendre pourquoi."

#. [message]: speaker=MC
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\02_Bandit_Camp.cfg:158
msgid "This is too slow, at this rate he will be lost to us!"
msgstr "Cela prend trop de temps, à cette vitesse-ci on ne le rattrapera pas!"

#. [scenario]: id=03_Merfolk_Party
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\03_Merfolk_Party.cfg:5
msgid "Merfolk Party"
msgstr "Groupe ondin"

#. [part]
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\03_Merfolk_Party.cfg:98
msgid ""
"The knights hurried after the mysterious figure and attempted to find out "
"who its was.\n"
"            \n"
"However, it proved elusive and its trail was lost north of the mountains."
msgstr ""
"Les chevaliers se hâtèrent aux trousses de la mystérieuse figure afin "
"d'apprendre son identité.\n"
"\n"
"Cependant, elle fut élusive et ils perdirent sa piste au nord des montagnes."

#. [part]
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\03_Merfolk_Party.cfg:103
msgid ""
"This was not all in vain however, for they encountered merfolk battling "
"bandits and dark mages at the source of the River Oumph."
msgstr ""
"Ceci ne fut pas complètement en vain malgré tout car ils rencontrèrent des "
"ondins combattant des bandits et des mages noirs à la source de la rivière "
"Oumph."

#. [part]
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\03_Merfolk_Party.cfg:106
msgid ""
"Chapter Three\n"
"<i>Merfolk Party</i>"
msgstr ""
"Chapitre Trois\n"
"<I>Groupe ondin</I>"

#. [message]: speaker=MP
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\03_Merfolk_Party.cfg:125
msgid "Hail, noble knights. What brings you here?"
msgstr "Salut, nobles chevaliers. Qu'est-ce qui vous amène ici?"

#. [message]: speaker=MC
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\03_Merfolk_Party.cfg:129
msgid ""
"Greetings to you, fair lady. We hunt bandits who have attacked human "
"villages south of here. They have eluded us, though others of their ilk seem "
"to have found their way to you."
msgstr ""
"Salutations, belle dame. Nous pourchassons des bandits ayant attaqué des "
"villages humains au sud d'ici. Ils nous ont échappés, cependant d'autres de "
"leur espèce semblent vous importuner."

#. [message]: speaker=MP
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\03_Merfolk_Party.cfg:133
msgid ""
"Indeed they have, and I would request your aid, for these ones wish to stop "
"us from heading downriver where their brethren are looting an ancient temple "
"hiding dark relics!"
msgstr ""
"Ils le font effectivement et je requerrais votre aide car ils souhaitent "
"nous empêcher de nous rendre en aval là où leurs confrères pillent un ancien "
"temple abritant des reliques maléfiques!"

#. [message]: speaker=MC
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\03_Merfolk_Party.cfg:137
msgid "Then we must provide assistance against these miscreants!"
msgstr "Il est de notre devoir de porter assistances contre ces mécréants!"

#. [message]: speaker=BL1
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\03_Merfolk_Party.cfg:149
msgid "I am sorry... m'lord..."
msgstr "Je suis désolé… mons'gneur..."

#. [message]: speaker=MP
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\03_Merfolk_Party.cfg:156
msgid "They were quite dedicated to their superiors."
msgstr "Ils étaient dédiés à leurs supérieurs."

#. [message]: speaker=MC
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\03_Merfolk_Party.cfg:160
msgid ""
"Ours were as well, perhaps they are of the same kind. In any case, let us "
"head north as fast as possible."
msgstr ""
"Ceux que nous pourchassions aussi. Peut-être sont-ils de la même espèce. En "
"tout cas, dirigeons-nous au nord avec hâte."

#. [message]: speaker=MP
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\03_Merfolk_Party.cfg:169
msgid "At this rate we shall never reach the temple in time!"
msgstr "À ce rythme nous n'atteindrons jamais le temple à temps!"

#. [scenario]: id=04_Temple_Assault
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\04_Temple_Assault.cfg:5
msgid "Temple Assault"
msgstr "Assaut du Temple"

#. [part]
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\04_Temple_Assault.cfg:98
msgid ""
"After encountering Lady Ariel and her merfolk troops, they all headed north, "
"to the mouth of the river and the temple located there.\n"
"            \n"
"All along, they pondered the motives of these bandits and the reason of "
"their loyalty to the one the caped figure represented, though they believed "
"they would soon obtain the answers."
msgstr ""
"Après avoir rencontré dame Ariel et ses troupes ondines, ils se dirigèrent "
"tous au nord, vers l'embouchure de la rivière et le temple situé là.\n"
"\n"
"Tout du long, ils se questionnèrent sur les motifs des bandits et la cause "
"de leur loyauté envers la personne que le personnage mystérieux "
"représentait. Ils pensaient cependant qu'ils obtiendraient bientôt des "
"réponses."

#. [part]
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\04_Temple_Assault.cfg:103
msgid ""
"Chapter Four\n"
"<i>Temple Assault</i>"
msgstr ""
"Chapitre Quatre\n"
"<I>Assaut du Temple</i>"

#. [label]
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\04_Temple_Assault.cfg:124
msgid "Ancient Temple"
msgstr "Temple antique"

#. [message]: speaker=MP
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\04_Temple_Assault.cfg:130
msgid "We have arrived. It seems they have already entered the temple!"
msgstr ""
"Nous sommes arrivés. Ils semblent avoir déjà pénétré à l'intérieur du temple!"

#. [message]: speaker=MC
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\04_Temple_Assault.cfg:134
msgid "In that case, we shall take them out!"
msgstr "Dans ce cas nous les en ferons sortir!"

#. [message]: speaker=BL2
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\04_Temple_Assault.cfg:138
msgid "Enemies are here, protect the master!"
msgstr "Des ennemis sont arrivés, protégez le maître!"

#. [message]: speaker=BL2
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\04_Temple_Assault.cfg:150
msgid "Master, we have failed you..."
msgstr "Maître, nous avons failli..."

#. [message]: speaker=MC
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\04_Temple_Assault.cfg:157
msgid "Finally, we shall find out what this is all about."
msgstr "Finalement, nous découvrirons les raisons de tout ceci."

#. [message]: speaker=MP
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\04_Temple_Assault.cfg:166
msgid "They will have stolen everything by the time we get in!"
msgstr "Ils auront tout pris d'ici à ce que nous puissions rentrer!"

#. [scenario]: id=05_Sacrilege
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\05_Sacrilege.cfg:5
msgid "Sacrilege"
msgstr "Sacrilège"

#. [part]
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\05_Sacrilege.cfg:70
msgid ""
"They entered the temple with all haste, that the enemy may be stopped.\n"
"            \n"
"Advancing through these ruins, they felt a chill permeate them, as though a "
"darkness was creeping through."
msgstr ""
"Ils entrèrent à l'intérieur du temple aussi rapidement que possible afin "
"d'arrêter les ennemis restants.\n"
"\n"
"En avançant dans ces ruines, ils sentirent un froid s'imprégner, comme si "
"les ténèbres les enveloppaient."

#. [part]
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\05_Sacrilege.cfg:75
msgid ""
"Chapter Five\n"
"<i>Sacrilege</i>"
msgstr ""
"Chapitre Cinq\n"
"<i>Sacrilège</i>"

#. [message]: speaker=MC
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\05_Sacrilege.cfg:101
msgid "Wait... You were conniving with the bandits raiding our villages!"
msgstr "Quoi? Vous étiez complices avec les bandits pillant nos villages!"

#. [message]: speaker=BBM
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\05_Sacrilege.cfg:105
msgid ""
"You... You killed quite a few of my master's servants... How annoying..."
msgstr ""
"Vous… Vous avez tuez bien des servants de mon maître... Très désagréable..."

#. [message]: speaker=MP
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\05_Sacrilege.cfg:109
msgid "What are you doing with these dark relics!"
msgstr "Que pensez-vous faire avec ces reliques maléfiques!"

#. [message]: speaker=BBM
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\05_Sacrilege.cfg:113
msgid "Taking them with me for the Crimson Duke has need of them."
msgstr "Les prendre avec moi car le Duc Pourpre en a besoin."

#. [message]: speaker=MC
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\05_Sacrilege.cfg:117
msgid "You shall do no such thing!"
msgstr "Vous ne ferez pas une telle chose!"

#. [message]: speaker=BBM
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\05_Sacrilege.cfg:121
msgid ""
"You have no way of stopping me, weakling. Now, do forgive me while I take my "
"leave."
msgstr ""
"Vous n'avez aucune façon de m'arrêter, insectes. Maintenant, veuillez "
"m'excuser de votre compagnie."

#. [message]: speaker=MP
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\05_Sacrilege.cfg:125
msgid "Return these to their place!"
msgstr "Remettez-les à leur place!"

#. [message]: speaker=BBH
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\05_Sacrilege.cfg:138
msgid "Aargh, the Light always hurts... Fools, try and catch me."
msgstr ""
"Aargh, la Lumière fait toujours mal... Imbéciles, essayez de m'arrêter."

#. [message]: speaker=MC
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\05_Sacrilege.cfg:150
msgid ""
"That was Baron Luroc, a retainer of Duke Myrraent! We have to arrest him!"
msgstr ""
"C'était le baron Luroc, un vassal du duc Myrraent! Nous devons le capturer!"

#. [scenario]: id=06_Shadows_Rise
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\06_Shadows_Rise.cfg:5
msgid "Shadows Rise"
msgstr "L'ombre croît"

#. [objective]: condition=win
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\06_Shadows_Rise.cfg:22
msgid "Hold until dawn"
msgstr "Tines jusqu'à l'aube"

#. [objectives]
#. [objective]: condition=win
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\06_Shadows_Rise.cfg:24
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\utils\misc.cfg:13
msgid "Defeat all enemy leaders"
msgstr "Vaincs tous les chefs ennemis"

#. [side]
#. [side]: id=HG, type=General
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\06_Shadows_Rise.cfg:54
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\07_Shore_Of_The_Avalynne.cfg:60
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\09a_Dawn_over_Dorest.cfg:74
msgid "Wesnoth"
msgstr "Wesnoth"

#. [part]
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\06_Shadows_Rise.cfg:90
msgid ""
"Though they tried, they failed to catch Baron Luroc within the temple and, "
"once outside, found no trace of him."
msgstr ""
"Bien qu'ils essayèrent, ils échouèrent à capturer le baron Luroc à "
"l'intérieur du temple et, une fois à l'extérieur, ne trouvèrent aucune trace "
"de lui."

#. [part]
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\06_Shadows_Rise.cfg:93
msgid ""
"They were thus left with no recourse but for the knights to head to Farzi, a "
"town within the fiefdom of Duke Myrraent, Luroc's suzerain, in the hopes of "
"informing him of his vassal's conniving with bandits and plundering of "
"forbidden artifacts."
msgstr ""
"Il n'y avait donc plus aucune option autre que pour les chevaliers de se "
"diriger vers Farzi, un village dans le fief du duc Myrraent, le suzerain de "
"Luroc, dans l'espoir de l'informer de la complicité de son vassal avec des "
"bandits et de son vols d'artéfacts ténébreux."

#. [part]
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\06_Shadows_Rise.cfg:96
msgid ""
"Chapter Six\n"
"<i>Shadows Rise</i>"
msgstr ""
"Chapitre Six\n"
"<i>L'ombre croît</i>"

#. [message]: speaker=MC
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\06_Shadows_Rise.cfg:128
msgid ""
"Hail, we are the Knights of the Silver Spire and we seek an audience with "
"Duke Myrraent on a matter of utmost import."
msgstr ""
"Salut, nous sommes les Chevaliers de la Tour d'Argent et requérons une "
"audience avec le duc Myrraent pour une affaire de la plus haute importance."

#. [message]: speaker=SP
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\06_Shadows_Rise.cfg:132
msgid "I shall inform him, please come in."
msgstr "Je vais l'informer de ce pas, vous pouvez entrer."

#. [message]: speaker=BBH
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\06_Shadows_Rise.cfg:166
msgid "My lord Myrraent is not here, might I be of assistance?"
msgstr "Monseigneur Myrraent n'est pas présent, puis-je vous être utile?"

#. [message]: speaker=MC
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\06_Shadows_Rise.cfg:170
msgid ""
"Baron Loruc, traitor to the Crown! We have evidence of your crimes against "
"the realm!"
msgstr ""
"Baron Luroc, traître à la couronne! Nous avons des preuves de vos crimes "
"envers le royaume!"

#. [message]: speaker=BBH
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\06_Shadows_Rise.cfg:174
msgid ""
"I have no time to deal with righteous fools like you. You shall not be "
"tolerated during our rise!"
msgstr ""
"Je n'au pas le temps de composer avec des fanatiques comme vous. Vous ne "
"serez pas toléré lors de notre retour!"

#. [modify_side]
#. [side]
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\06_Shadows_Rise.cfg:191
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\06_Shadows_Rise.cfg:212
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\07_Shore_Of_The_Avalynne.cfg:74
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\07_Shore_Of_The_Avalynne.cfg:147
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\08a_Light_In_The_Dark.cfg:45
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\09a_Dawn_over_Dorest.cfg:50
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\09b_Alight_From_All_Sides.cfg:59
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\09c_Death_Amongst_The_Trees.cfg:53
msgid "Vampires"
msgstr "Vampires"

#. [message]: speaker=BB
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\06_Shadows_Rise.cfg:219
msgid "I shall enjoy turning you all. Now, let us end this charade."
msgstr "J'apprécierai de vous corrompre tous. Finissons donc cette charade."

#. [message]: speaker=MC
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\06_Shadows_Rise.cfg:223
msgid ""
"Vampires! To battle, everyone! Protect the citizenry and hold until day that "
"we might banish these corpses!"
msgstr ""
"Vampires! Aux armes, compagnons! Protégez les villageois et tenons jusqu'à "
"l'aube afin de bannir ces morts-vivants!"

#. [message]: speaker=BB
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\06_Shadows_Rise.cfg:227
msgid "Tis not for the rabble you should fear."
msgstr "Ce n'est pas pour la vermine que vous devriez vous inquiéter."

#. [message]: speaker=MC
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\06_Shadows_Rise.cfg:294
msgid "What have you done, you monster!"
msgstr "Qu'avez-vous fait, monstre!"

#. [message]: speaker=BB
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\06_Shadows_Rise.cfg:298
msgid ""
"They have been given a boon they did not deserve that they may better serve "
"our Master."
msgstr ""
"Ils ont reçu un présent inespéré qu'ils ne méritaient pas afin de mieux "
"servir notre Maître."

#. [message]: speaker=unit
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\06_Shadows_Rise.cfg:308
msgid "This should stem the flow a little..."
msgstr "Ceci devrait endiguer le flot un petit peu..."

#. [message]: speaker=BB
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\06_Shadows_Rise.cfg:320
msgid ""
"No, I will not fall here! You have no chance, the sun will not rise and my "
"minions shall end you!"
msgstr ""
"Non, je ne tomberai pas ici! Vous n'avez aucune chance, le soleil ne se "
"lèvera pas et mes servants vous tuerons!"

#. [message]: speaker=MC
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\06_Shadows_Rise.cfg:324
msgid ""
"His hordes are indeed numerous, prepare to withdraw and call upon aid from "
"Dorest."
msgstr ""
"Ces hordes sont effectivement nombreuses. Préparons-nous à battre en "
"retraite et à demander de l'aide de Dorest."

#. [message]: speaker=MC
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\06_Shadows_Rise.cfg:336
msgid "It should be day by now and yet no sign of the sun..."
msgstr "Il devrait déjà faire jour et pourtant aucun signe du soleil..."

#. [message]: speaker=BB
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\06_Shadows_Rise.cfg:340
msgid "I did not pilfer these artifacts without a reason."
msgstr "Je n'ai pris ces artéfacts sans raison."

#. [message]: speaker=MC
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\06_Shadows_Rise.cfg:344
msgid ""
"We are being swarmed and there is little room to maneuver... Fall back, we "
"are at a disadvantage in this battle!"
msgstr ""
"Nous sommes attaqués de toute part et il y a peu d'espace pour manœuvrer… "
"Battons en retraite, nous sommes à un désavantage lors de cette bataille!"

#. [message]: speaker=BB
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\06_Shadows_Rise.cfg:365
msgid "Good, another thrall for our forces."
msgstr "Bien, un autre esclave pour nos forces."

#. [message]: speaker=unit
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\06_Shadows_Rise.cfg:369
msgid ""
"I may fall but I am shielded by the Light, I shall never serve your kind!"
msgstr ""
"Je meurs peut-être mais je suis protégé par la Lumière, je ne servirai "
"jamais votre espèce!"

#. [message]: speaker=BB
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\06_Shadows_Rise.cfg:384
msgid "Foolish zealots... We won't be able to turn them..."
msgstr "Stupide zélotes… Nous ne pourrons pas les corrompre..."

#. [scenario]: id=07_Shore_Of_The_Avalynne
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\07_Shore_Of_The_Avalynne.cfg:5
msgid "Shore of the Avalynne"
msgstr "Rive de l'Avalynne"

#. [objective]: condition=win
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\07_Shore_Of_The_Avalynne.cfg:26
msgid "Kill as many enemies as possible before Vaedyr dies"
msgstr "Tue autant d'ennemis que possible avant que Vaedyr ne meurs"

#. [objectives]
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\07_Shore_Of_The_Avalynne.cfg:28
msgid "Defeat an enemy leader"
msgstr "Vaincs un chef ennemi"

#. [note]
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\07_Shore_Of_The_Avalynne.cfg:31
msgid ""
"Losses are irrelevant. The scenario ends when a leader (Vaedyr or an enemy) "
"dies."
msgstr ""
"Les pertes sont sans conséquence. Le scénario se termine lorsqu'un chef "
"(Vaedyr ou un ennemi) meurs."

#. [part]
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\07_Shore_Of_The_Avalynne.cfg:93
msgid ""
"The knights rode for a lightless day, heading southwest towards Dorest to "
"warn of the threat, with the vampires hot on their trail."
msgstr ""
"Les chevaliers chevauchèrent pour un jour sans lumière, se dirigeant au sud-"
"ouest vers Dorest pour avertir de la menace, avec des vampires les "
"poursuivant de près."

#. [part]
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\07_Shore_Of_The_Avalynne.cfg:96
msgid ""
"However, they encountered other enemies before the crossing of the Avalynne."
msgstr ""
"Cependant, ils rencontrèrent d'autres ennemis avant la traversée de "
"l'Avalynne."

#. [part]
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\07_Shore_Of_The_Avalynne.cfg:99
msgid ""
"Chapter Seven\n"
"<i>Shore of the Avalynne</i>"
msgstr ""
"Chapitre Sept\n"
"<i>Rive de l'Avalynne</i>"

#. [message]: speaker=CDH
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\07_Shore_Of_The_Avalynne.cfg:116
msgid "What have we here? Knights running away from someone?"
msgstr "Qu'avons-nous ici? Des chevaliers fuyant quelqu'un?"

#. [message]: speaker=MC
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\07_Shore_Of_The_Avalynne.cfg:120
msgid ""
"Duke Myrraent, you arrive at a most opportune time. We were heading to "
"Dorest to warn of Baron Luroc's treachery but it seems this was unnecessary "
"as you may assist us against him!"
msgstr ""
"Duc Myrraent, vous arrivez à un moment plus qu'opportun. Nous nous dirigions "
"vers Dorest pour avertir de la traîtrise du baron Luroc mais il semble que "
"cela ne soit pas nécessaire puisque vous pouvez nous aider contre lui!"

#. [message]: speaker=CDH
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\07_Shore_Of_The_Avalynne.cfg:124
msgid ""
"That is a most serious accusation towards one of my vassals. Pray tell, what "
"crime has he commited?"
msgstr ""
"Cette accusation envers un de mes vassaux est des plus sérieuse. Dites-moi "
"donc, quel crime a-t-il commis?"

#. [message]: speaker=MC
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\07_Shore_Of_The_Avalynne.cfg:128
msgid ""
"Not only is he in leagues with the bandits led by the Crimson Duke who have "
"ransacked multiple villages but he is also a vile vampire!"
msgstr ""
"Non seulement est-il allié aux bandits menés par le Duc Pourpre qui ont mis "
"à sac plusieurs villages mais il est aussi un infâme vampire!"

#. [message]: speaker=CDH
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\07_Shore_Of_The_Avalynne.cfg:132
msgid ""
"Alas, I must decline your request. Knights have always bored me, hunting our "
"kind... And they are so reluctant to obey their betters, unlike common "
"bandits, right, Baron?"
msgstr ""
"Malheureusement, je dois décliner votre requête. Les chevaliers m'ont "
"toujours embêté, chassant les mieux… Et ils sont toujours si peu disposés à "
"obéir à des être supérieurs, contrairement aux bandits, n'est-ce pas, baron?"

#. [message]: speaker=BB
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\07_Shore_Of_The_Avalynne.cfg:152
msgid "Indeed, sire. The highwaymen proved most amenable, unlike this rabble."
msgstr ""
"Effectivement, sir. Les brigands se sont montrés des plus serviables, "
"contrairement à ces vauriens."

#. [message]: speaker=MC
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\07_Shore_Of_The_Avalynne.cfg:156
msgid ""
"You are the Crimson Duke? You have been organizing these bandit raids for "
"months!"
msgstr ""
"Vous êtes le Duc Pourpre? Vous avez organisés ces attaques de bandits "
"pendant des mois!"

#. [message]: speaker=CD
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\07_Shore_Of_The_Avalynne.cfg:160
msgid ""
"Indeed I have, that the kingdom might learn to fear my name. Now submit to "
"superior beings else we shall feast on your blood!"
msgstr ""
"Effectivement c'était moi. Il fallait bien que le royaume apprenne à "
"craindre mon nom. Maintenant soumettez-vous à des êtres supérieurs, sinon "
"nous souperons avec votre sang!"

#. [message]: speaker=MC
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\07_Shore_Of_The_Avalynne.cfg:164
msgid ""
"We are the knights of the Silver Spire and shall never bow to evil! We may "
"be fated to die but we shall not go quietly! Brothers, kill as many as you "
"can, for Wesnoth and for the Light!"
msgstr ""
"Nous sommes les Chevaliers de la Tour d'Argent ne nous rendrons jamais au "
"mal! Nous sommes peut-être destinés à mourir mais nous ne le ferons pas "
"silencieusement! Compagnons, tuez-en autaunt que possible, pour Wesnoth et "
"la Lumière!"

#. [message]: speaker=MC
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\07_Shore_Of_The_Avalynne.cfg:205
msgid "Fight on! Kill... more of... them..."
msgstr "Continuez! Tuez… en… plus..."

#. [message]: speaker=CD
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\07_Shore_Of_The_Avalynne.cfg:227
msgid "Foolish humans, they believed they could harm us... How laughable!"
msgstr ""
"Stupides humains, ils croyaient qu'ils pouvaient nous porter atteint… "
"Risible!"

#. [message]: speaker=BB
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\07_Shore_Of_The_Avalynne.cfg:231
msgid "What should we do with them sire, for they cannot be turned easily."
msgstr ""
"Que devrions-nous faire avec eux sire, car ils seront difficiles à "
"transformer."

#. [message]: speaker=CD
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\07_Shore_Of_The_Avalynne.cfg:235
msgid ""
"Kill those who remain then stay here and work on dispelling their "
"protections. Hold the rear guard while I head to Dorest."
msgstr ""
"Tuez ceux qui respirent encore puis reste ici et occupes-toi de dissiper "
"leurs protections. Tiens l'arrière-garde pendant que je me dirige vers "
"Dorest."

#. [message]: speaker=CD
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\07_Shore_Of_The_Avalynne.cfg:252
msgid "You are... but... mortals, this is... impossible!"
msgstr "Vous n'êtes… que des... mortels, ceci est... impossible!"

#. [message]: speaker=MC
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\07_Shore_Of_The_Avalynne.cfg:256
msgid "Now to his lackey!"
msgstr "Maintenant son laquais!"

#. [message]: speaker=BB
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\07_Shore_Of_The_Avalynne.cfg:260
msgid "This cannot be happening, fall back to Farzi!"
msgstr "Ceci ne peut arriver, fuyons vers Farzi!"

#. [message]: speaker=BB
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\07_Shore_Of_The_Avalynne.cfg:278
msgid "How, you are but wretched humans!"
msgstr "Comment, vous n'êtes que de misérables humains!"

#. [message]: speaker=MC
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\07_Shore_Of_The_Avalynne.cfg:286
msgid "Onwards, break them!"
msgstr "En avant, brisez leur lignes!"

#. [message]: speaker=CD
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\07_Shore_Of_The_Avalynne.cfg:290
msgid ""
"We have not the strength to take Dorest without the artifact, fall back!"
msgstr ""
"Nous n'avons pas la force pour prendre Dorest sans l'artéfact, retraite!"

#. [scenario]: id=08a_Light_In_The_Dark
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\08a_Light_In_The_Dark.cfg:5
msgid "Light in the Dark"
msgstr "Lumière dans les ténèbres"

#. [side]
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\08a_Light_In_The_Dark.cfg:32
msgid "Merfolk"
msgstr "Ondins"

#. [part]
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\08a_Light_In_The_Dark.cfg:69
msgid ""
"Though the knights had arrived first, they were not the only one that were "
"heading at the Avalynne."
msgstr ""
"Bien que les chevaliers soient arrivés les premiers, ils n'étaient pas les "
"seuls qui se dirigeaient vers l'Avalynne."

#. [part]
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\08a_Light_In_The_Dark.cfg:72
msgid ""
"Chapter Eight\n"
"<i>Light In The Dark</i>"
msgstr ""
"Chapitre Huit\n"
"<i>Lumière dans les ténèbres</i>"

#. [message]: speaker=MP
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\08a_Light_In_The_Dark.cfg:91
msgid ""
"Monsters... I had surmised what you were when we passed Farzi but I still "
"did not truly believe I would find bloodsuckers at the end of the knight's "
"trail."
msgstr ""
"Monstres… J'avais deviné ce que vous étiez lorsque nous passâmes Farzi mais "
"je ne croyais pas réellement rencontrer des suceurs de sang à la fin de la "
"piste des chevaliers."

#. [message]: speaker=BB
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\08a_Light_In_The_Dark.cfg:95
msgid "Water scum... It seems your hopes were misplaced."
msgstr ""
"Racaille aquatique… Il semblerait que vos espoirs aient été mal placés."

#. [message]: speaker=MP
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\08a_Light_In_The_Dark.cfg:99
msgid ""
"I shall not let you desecrate their corpses and profane their souls! You "
"will fall to the Light!"
msgstr ""
"Je ne vous laisserai pas profaner leurs corps et leurs âmes! Vous tomberez "
"face à la Lumière!"

#. [message]: speaker=BB
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\08a_Light_In_The_Dark.cfg:103
msgid "Fools, all of you..."
msgstr "Idiots, tous autant que vous êtes..."

#. [message]: speaker=MP
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\08a_Light_In_The_Dark.cfg:107
msgid ""
"Your fell spells occupy you. You will have no strength for battle and we "
"shall destroy you!"
msgstr ""
"Vos sombres sorts vous occupe. Vous n'aurez pas de force pour un combat et "
"nous vous anéantirons!"

#. [message]: speaker=BB
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\08a_Light_In_The_Dark.cfg:119
msgid "Impossible, we are superior!"
msgstr "Impossible, nous sommes supérieurs!"

#. [message]: speaker=MP
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\08a_Light_In_The_Dark.cfg:126
msgid "The darkness has receded, now let us banish its remains."
msgstr "La noirceur s'estompe, maintenant que ses restes sois bannis."

#. [message]: speaker=MP
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\08a_Light_In_The_Dark.cfg:135
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\08b_Soothing_Sight.cfg:95
msgid ""
"I beseech you, o great Light, grant your blessings upon these brave knights "
"who sacrificed themselves against your foes, that they may yet have a chance "
"to save their people."
msgstr ""
"Je t'implore, ô bienveillante Lumière, accorde ta bénédiction à ces braves "
"soldats qui se sont sacrifiés contre tes ennemis, qu'ils aient une chance de "
"sauver les leurs."

#. [message]: speaker=MC
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\08a_Light_In_The_Dark.cfg:157
msgid ""
"Thank you for this hope, it shall not go to waste! (<i>To the other knights</"
"i>) The <i>Crimson Duke</i> is probably heading for Dorest as we speak! We "
"ride with all haste!"
msgstr ""
"Merci pour cet espoir, ils ne sera pas gâché! (<i>Aux autres chevaliers</"
"i>)Le Duc Pourpre se dirige probablement vers Dorest à ce moment même! Nous "
"chevauchons à totue vitesse!"

#. [message]: speaker=MP
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\08a_Light_In_The_Dark.cfg:161
msgid "May you succeed in your quest!"
msgstr "Puissiez-vous réussir dans votre quête!"

#. [message]: speaker=$this_item.id
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\08a_Light_In_The_Dark.cfg:169
msgid "What miracle is this!"
msgstr "Quel miracle vient-il d'arriver!"

#. [message]: speaker=BB
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\08a_Light_In_The_Dark.cfg:178
msgid "That should be enough, they will now rise with us!"
msgstr "Ceci devrait être suffisant, ils se battront à nos côtés!"

#. [scenario]: id=08b_Soothing_Sight
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\08b_Soothing_Sight.cfg:5
msgid "Soothing Sight"
msgstr "Scène réconfortante"

#. [part]
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\08b_Soothing_Sight.cfg:55
msgid ""
"After this hard-won battle, the knights regrouped to prepare to give chase "
"to the vampire forces' remains.\n"
"            \n"
"However, before they could depart, other allies appeared."
msgstr ""
"Après cette bataille âprement gagnée, les chevaliers se regroupèrent pour "
"préparer la poursuite des survivants des vampires.\n"
"\n"
"Cependant, avant qu'ils ne lancent la chasse, d'autres alliés apparurent."

#. [part]
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\08b_Soothing_Sight.cfg:60
msgid ""
"After all, though the knights had arrived first, they were not the only one "
"that were heading upriver."
msgstr ""
"Après tout, bien que les chevaliers soient arrivés en premier, ils n'étaient "
"pas les seuls à se diriger en amont."

#. [part]
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\08b_Soothing_Sight.cfg:63
msgid ""
"Chapter Eight\n"
"<i>Soothing Light</i>"
msgstr ""
"Chapitre Huit\n"
"<i>Scène réconfortante</i>"

#. [message]: speaker=MP
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\08b_Soothing_Sight.cfg:83
msgid ""
"Dear knights, I am overjoyed to see you again. When we passed Farzi and saw  "
"signs of battle, I feared the worst."
msgstr ""
"Chers chevaliers, je suis ravie de vous revoir. Quand nous avions passé "
"Farzi et que j'ai vu les signes de combat, j'ai craint le pire."

#. [message]: speaker=MC
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\08b_Soothing_Sight.cfg:87
msgid ""
"I thank you for your concern, fair lady, though happily it was unwarranted, "
"for though we lost many, we routed the enemy. However, I fear not enough of "
"us are left for the next battle."
msgstr ""
"Je vous remercie pour vos préoccupations, belle dame. Heureusement elles "
"furent superflues car bien que nous ayons perdu beaucoup des nôtres, nous "
"avons mis l'ennemi en déroute. Cependant, j'ai bien peur que ces pertes "
"soient trop élevées..."

#. [message]: speaker=MP
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\08b_Soothing_Sight.cfg:91
msgid ""
"Left alone, the vampires would still pose a grave threat to all within the "
"North, and the Light shall not allow this to be so."
msgstr ""
"Laissés à eux-mêmes, les vampires poseraient encore un péril majeur pour "
"tous ceux vivant dans le Nord et la Lumière ne permettra pas qu'un tel "
"danger existe."

#. [message]: speaker=MC
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\08b_Soothing_Sight.cfg:113
msgid ""
"Unbelievable! Thank you from the bottom of our hearts, o Lady of Light, for "
"with this boon, we have a chance of ridding the land of these abominations."
msgstr ""
"Incroyable! Nous vous remercions du fond du cœur, ô dame de la Lumière, car "
"avec cette bénédiction nous pourrons débarrasser cette terre de ces "
"abominations."

#. [message]: speaker=MP
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\08b_Soothing_Sight.cfg:117
msgid "Let it be so. Pray tell, where are their remnants headed?"
msgstr "Qu'il en soit ainsi. Vers où vont-ils?"

#. [message]: speaker=MC
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\08b_Soothing_Sight.cfg:128
msgid "The Bloody Baron headed northeast, towards Farzi."
msgstr "Le Baron Sanglant s'est dirigé vers le nord-est, vers Farzi."

#. [message]: speaker=MP
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\08b_Soothing_Sight.cfg:132
msgid ""
"I had left some of my party there, if we hurry we may yet catch them before "
"they reach their fortress!"
msgstr ""
"J'avais laissé certaines de mes troupes là-bas, si nous nous dépêchons nous "
"pourrions les prendre à revers!"

#. [message]: speaker=MC
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\08b_Soothing_Sight.cfg:147
msgid "The Crimson Duke headed west, towards the Greenwood."
msgstr ""
"Le Duc Pourpre se dirigea vers l'ouest, dans la direction de la Forêt Verte."

#. [message]: speaker=MP
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\08b_Soothing_Sight.cfg:151
msgid ""
"Take care, for those who hide within are no friends to other races. Nor are "
"they even to their own."
msgstr ""
"Faites attention, car ceux qui y vivent ne sont les amis de personne, pas "
"même des autres elfes."

#. [message]: speaker=MC
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\08b_Soothing_Sight.cfg:155
msgid "I thank you for your warning, I shall take it to heart. Farewell!"
msgstr ""
"Je vous remercie pour votre avertissement, il sera pris à cœur. Au revoir!"

#. [scenario]: id=09a_Dawn_over_Dorest
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\09a_Dawn_over_Dorest.cfg:5
msgid "Dawn over Dorest"
msgstr "Aube à Dorest"

#. [part]
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\09a_Dawn_over_Dorest.cfg:99
msgid ""
"The knights sped with all haste towards Dorest, that they might stop the "
"Crimson Duke's evil designs from taking form."
msgstr ""
"Les chevaliers galopèrent à toute allure vers Dorest afin de mettre un terme "
"aux maléfiques desseins du Duc Pourpre."

#. [part]
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\09a_Dawn_over_Dorest.cfg:102
msgid ""
"This was a pressing task for the battle was already fierce in front of the "
"city's walls."
msgstr ""
"C'était une tâche pressante car la battaile faisait déjà rage devant les "
"murs de la ville."

#. [part]
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\09a_Dawn_over_Dorest.cfg:105
msgid ""
"Chapter Nine\n"
"<i>Dawn over Dorest</i>"
msgstr ""
"Chapitre Neuf\n"
"<i>Aube à Dorest</i>"

#. [message]: speaker=HG
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\09a_Dawn_over_Dorest.cfg:127
msgid "Nooo... The city..."
msgstr "Noon... La ville..."

#. [message]: speaker=CD
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\09a_Dawn_over_Dorest.cfg:131
msgid "Finally, this futile resistance is over."
msgstr "Finalement, cette futile résistance n'a plus court."

#. [message]: speaker=MC
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\09a_Dawn_over_Dorest.cfg:135
msgid ""
"The city is lost and without it, the North is cut off from Wesnoth, we have "
"failed!"
msgstr ""
"La ville est perdue et sans elle, le Nord est coupé de Wesnoth, nous avons "
"failli!"

#. [label]
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\09a_Dawn_over_Dorest.cfg:149
msgid "Silver Spire"
msgstr "Tour d'Argent"

#. [message]: speaker=HG
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\09a_Dawn_over_Dorest.cfg:155
msgid ""
"Who are you, accursed monster, and why do you trouble our fair city? ..."
"Wait ...Duke Myrraent, is that you?"
msgstr ""
"Qui êtes-vous, monstre, et pourquoi attaquez-vous notre cité?... Une "
"seconde… Duc Myrraent, est-ce vous?"

#. [message]: speaker=CD
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\09a_Dawn_over_Dorest.cfg:159
msgid ""
"I have thrown away that fake mask. I am the Crimson Duke and you shall all "
"fall at my feet! Now, despair!"
msgstr ""
"J'ai rejeté ce faux nom. Je suis le Duc Pourpre et vous tomberez tous à mes "
"pieds!"

#. [message]: speaker=HG
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\09a_Dawn_over_Dorest.cfg:163
msgid ""
"You stand against the kingdom of Wesnoth and have no hope of victory on this "
"day!"
msgstr ""
"Vous vous dressez contre le royaume de Wesnoth et n'avez aucune chance de "
"triompher!"

#. [message]: speaker=CD
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\09a_Dawn_over_Dorest.cfg:167
msgid ""
"I do not recognize the authority of your pitiful king! You shall all bow "
"down to me!"
msgstr ""
"Je ne reconnais pas l'autorité de votre minable roi! Vous vous inclinerez "
"tous devant moI!"

#. [message]: speaker=MC
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\09a_Dawn_over_Dorest.cfg:171
msgid "Your dark crusade ends here, Crimson Duke!"
msgstr "Votre sombre croisade s'arrête aujourd'hui, Duc Pourpre!"

#. [message]: speaker=CD
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\09a_Dawn_over_Dorest.cfg:175
msgid "The Knights of the Silver Spire... Did I not slay you all?"
msgstr "Les Chevaliers de la Tour d'Argent… Ne vous avais-je pas tous tués?"

#. [message]: speaker=MC
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\09a_Dawn_over_Dorest.cfg:179
msgid ""
"The Light does not falter. Your servant is dead and so shall you soon be!"
msgstr ""
"La Lumière ne fléchit pas. Votre servant est mort et vous le serez bientôt!"

#. [message]: speaker=CD
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\09a_Dawn_over_Dorest.cfg:183
msgid ""
"Go ahead and try, little whelps. The night will soon return and, when it "
"does, you will all die..."
msgstr ""
"Essayez si vous pouvez. La nuit arrivera bientôt et quand elle sera de "
"retour, vous mourrez tous..."

#. [message]: speaker=CD
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\09a_Dawn_over_Dorest.cfg:195
msgid "Impossible, deafeated by these wretches!"
msgstr "Impossible, vaincu par des misérables humains!"

#. [message]: speaker=MC
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\09a_Dawn_over_Dorest.cfg:199
msgid "Face the wrath of the Light!"
msgstr "Souffrez la fureur de la Lumière!"

#. [message]: speaker=MC
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\09a_Dawn_over_Dorest.cfg:211
msgid "He shall haunt this land no longer."
msgstr "Il ne hantera plus cette terre."

#. [message]: speaker=HG
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\09a_Dawn_over_Dorest.cfg:215
msgid ""
"You have our utmost gratitude, oh Knights of the Silver Spire, for you have "
"saved the Northlands and, perhaps, the realm itself from a dark fate."
msgstr ""
"Vous avez notre extrême gratitude, ô Chevaliers de la Tour d'Argent, car "
"vous avez sauvé le Nord et peut-être même le royaume lui-même d'une sombre "
"destinée."

#. [message]: speaker=unit
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\09a_Dawn_over_Dorest.cfg:232
msgid "How, we slew you!"
msgstr "Comment, nous vous avons tué!"

#. [message]: speaker=second_unit
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\09a_Dawn_over_Dorest.cfg:236
msgid "Begone, foul corpse!"
msgstr "Disparaissez, infâme cadavre!"

#. [message]: speaker=CD
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\09a_Dawn_over_Dorest.cfg:246
msgid "With the night on my side I am unstoppable! You have no chance!"
msgstr ""
"Avec la nuit à mes côtés je suis invincible! Vous n'avez aucune chance!"

#. [scenario]: id=09b_Alight_From_All_Sides
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\09b_Alight_From_All_Sides.cfg:5
msgid "Alight From All Sides"
msgstr "Attaqués de toute part"

#. [part]
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\09b_Alight_From_All_Sides.cfg:83
msgid ""
"The vampires had suffered a devastating blow with the loss of their leader "
"and were now on the run, fleeing towards their lair at Farzi.\n"
"            \n"
"They hoped to weather the storm headed their way within the walls of the "
"fortified isle."
msgstr ""
"Les vampires avaient subit un revers dévastateur avec la perte de leur chef "
"et étaient maintenant en fuite, courant vers leur repaire à Farzi.\n"
"\n"
"Ils espéraient survivre aux forces dirigées vers eux derrière les murs de "
"leur île fortifiée."

#. [part]
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\09b_Alight_From_All_Sides.cfg:88
msgid ""
"They, however, had not expected merfolk to hold them back and keep them from "
"reaching their haven until the knights arrived to finish them off."
msgstr ""
"Ils ne s'attendaient cependant pas à des odins les retenant et les empêchant "
"de rejoindre leur refuge avant que les chevaliers n'arrivent pour les "
"exterminer."

#. [part]
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\09b_Alight_From_All_Sides.cfg:91
msgid ""
"Chapter Nine\n"
"<i>Alight From All Sides</i>"
msgstr ""
"Chapitre Neuf\n"
"<i>Attaqués de toute part</i>"

#. [message]: speaker=BB
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\09b_Alight_From_All_Sides.cfg:110
msgid "Hurry and kill this vermin! We need to reach the island!"
msgstr "Dépêchez et tuez cette vermine! Nous devons rejoindre l'île!"

#. [message]: speaker=MP
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\09b_Alight_From_All_Sides.cfg:114
msgid ""
"You will not reach safety, vampire. All that awaits you is a final death."
msgstr ""
"Vous n'atteindrez pas la sûreté, vampire. Tout ce qui vous attend est une "
"dernière mort."

#. [message]: speaker=BB
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\09b_Alight_From_All_Sides.cfg:118
msgid ""
"Foolish mermaid, you face beings far older than you. You are not feared here."
msgstr ""
"Stupide sirène, vous faites face à des êtres bien plus anciens que vous. Nul "
"n'a peur de vous ici."

#. [message]: speaker=MC
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\09b_Alight_From_All_Sides.cfg:122
msgid ""
"Fear is irrelevant, today you will be eradicated. We, the knights of the "
"Silver Spire, swear so!"
msgstr ""
"La peur est sans importance, aujourd'hui vous serez éradicés. Nous, les "
"Chevaliers de la Tour d'Argent, le jurons!"

#. [message]: speaker=BB
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\09b_Alight_From_All_Sides.cfg:126
msgid "Human scum! Kill them all!"
msgstr "Racaille humaine! Massacrez-les tous!"

#. [message]: speaker=BB
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\09b_Alight_From_All_Sides.cfg:138
msgid "No... Impossible... Not against wretches like you..."
msgstr "Non... Impossible.. Pas contre des vermines comme vous..."

#. [message]: speaker=MC
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\09b_Alight_From_All_Sides.cfg:149
msgid ""
"He is dead, we need only finish off the last remains of his despicable ilk. "
"The world will be better off without them. I must thank you for your "
"inestimable assistance against them."
msgstr ""
"Il est mort, nous n'avons plus qu'à tuer les vestiges de son odieux genre. "
"Le monde sera meilleur sans eux. Je dois vous remercier pour votre "
"inestimable assistance contre eux."

#. [message]: speaker=MP
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\09b_Alight_From_All_Sides.cfg:153
msgid ""
"No thanks are necessary, for though he threatened humans now, we would soon "
"have been at risk."
msgstr ""
"Aucun remerciement n'est nécessaire car, bien qu'ils aient surtout menacés "
"des humains, tous auraient été à risque."

#. [message]: speaker=MC
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\09b_Alight_From_All_Sides.cfg:157
msgid ""
"Well then, I shall have to report this to the lords in Dorest. May we meet "
"again!"
msgstr ""
"Je vais relater les évènements aux seigneurs de Dorest. Puissions-nous nous "
"rencontrer à nouveau!"

#. [message]: speaker=MP
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\09b_Alight_From_All_Sides.cfg:161
msgid "The same to you!"
msgstr "De même pour vous!"

#. [scenario]: id=09c_Death_Amongst_The_Trees
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\09c_Death_Amongst_The_Trees.cfg:5
msgid "Death Amongst The Trees"
msgstr "Mort parmi les arbres"

#. [objective]: condition=win
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\09c_Death_Amongst_The_Trees.cfg:22
msgid "Death of the Crimson Duke"
msgstr "Mort du Duc Pourpre"

#. [side]: id=EL, type=Elvish High Lord
#. [side]: id=ES, type=Elvish Sylph
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\09c_Death_Amongst_The_Trees.cfg:67
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\09c_Death_Amongst_The_Trees.cfg:83
msgid "Elves"
msgstr "Elfes"

#. [part]
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\09c_Death_Amongst_The_Trees.cfg:104
msgid ""
"With the death of their Bloody Baron and the destruction of the dark "
"artifact that had been casting a shadow over the battlefield, the "
"nightborn's plans were shattered and they had no choice but to retreat."
msgstr ""
"Avec la mort du Baron Sanglant et la destruction de l'obscur artifact qui "
"jetait une ombre sur le champ de bataille , les plans des vampires ont volé "
"en éclats et ils n'eurent d'autre choix que la retraite."

#. [part]
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\09c_Death_Amongst_The_Trees.cfg:107
msgid ""
"They fled west, towards the Greenwood, without thinking of the cruel beings "
"who dwelled there."
msgstr ""
"Ils fuirent vers l'ouest et la Forêt Verte sans penser aux êtres cruels y "
"vivant."

#. [part]
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\09c_Death_Amongst_The_Trees.cfg:110
msgid ""
"Chapter Nine\n"
"<i>Death Amongst The Trees</i>"
msgstr ""
"Chapitre Neuf\n"
"<i>Mort parmi les arbres</i>"

#. [message]: speaker=EL
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\09c_Death_Amongst_The_Trees.cfg:129
msgid "Fell being, pray tell, what do you seek in these woods but death?"
msgstr "Sombre être, dites, que cherchez-vous dans ces bois à part votre mort?"

#. [message]: speaker=CD
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\09c_Death_Amongst_The_Trees.cfg:133
msgid "Nothing from you, foolish elf."
msgstr "Rien de vous, bête elfe."

#. [message]: speaker=ES
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\09c_Death_Amongst_The_Trees.cfg:137
msgid ""
"You have stepped within our forest, abomination that was once a man, and for "
"that you shall die."
msgstr ""
"Vous êtes entré dans notre forêt, abomination qui fut un homme, et pour cela "
"vous mourrez."

#. [message]: speaker=MC
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\09c_Death_Amongst_The_Trees.cfg:141
msgid ""
"Already making new enemies... dear Crimson Duke, perhaps that will be your "
"end."
msgstr ""
"Déjà en train de se faire de nouveaux ennemis… cher Duc Pourpre, peut-être "
"que cela sera la raison de votre fin."

#. [message]: speaker=EL
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\09c_Death_Amongst_The_Trees.cfg:145
msgid "Humans here! more fools to kill I see..."
msgstr "Des humains ici! Je vois, plus de sots à tuer..."

#. [message]: speaker=ES
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\09c_Death_Amongst_The_Trees.cfg:149
msgid "Let us first handle the monsters, then we shall focus on the beasts."
msgstr "Occupons-nous d'abord des monstres, après des bêtes."

#. [message]: speaker=CD
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\09c_Death_Amongst_The_Trees.cfg:161
msgid "No! We were destined for more than this!"
msgstr "Non! Nous étions destinés pour plus!"

#. [message]: speaker=MC
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\09c_Death_Amongst_The_Trees.cfg:171
msgid "I thank you for the slaying of this monster."
msgstr "Je vous remercie pour la mort de ce monstre."

#. [message]: speaker=ES
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\09c_Death_Amongst_The_Trees.cfg:175
msgid ""
"Do not dare speak to me, animal! We rejected your kind and for that were "
"banished! Now you intrude upon our domain and for that you shall pay!"
msgstr ""
"N'osez pas me parler, animal! ous avons rejeté les vôtres et pour cela "
"furent bannis! Maintenant vous envahissez notre domaine et pour cela vous "
"payerez!"

#. [message]: speaker=MC
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\09c_Death_Amongst_The_Trees.cfg:179
msgid ""
"I am sorry for this state of affair but I have no desire for battle when it "
"is unneeded. (<i>To the knights</i>) Fall back, we retreat!"
msgstr ""
"Je suis désolé pour l'état des choses mais n'ai aucun désir pour une "
"bataille inutile. (<i>Aux chevaliers</i>) Retraite!"

#. [scenario]: id=10_Epilogue
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\10_Epilogue.cfg:5
msgid "Epilogue"
msgstr "Épilogue"

#. [part]
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\10_Epilogue.cfg:58
msgid ""
"In the Greenwood, between the shadow of the trees, the three-way battle had "
"now ended with the death of the vampires, their Crimson Duke fallen as if "
"pierced by the very light he had tried to scatter away, all that remained of "
"him a corpse upon the ground, food for worms and no trouble for anyone "
"anymore.\n"
"\n"
"Now the elves faced other foes, for though it had been almost two hundred "
"years since the civil war and their banishment with few left alive from that "
"time, their hatred of mankind still ran deep.\n"
"\n"
"However, today was not to be a day of reckoning, for the human intruders "
"withdrew as fast as possible, seeing no reason to fight a battle they did "
"not want.\n"
"\n"
"On that day, the Knights of the Silver Spire avoided a battle against fellow "
"living beings and, perhaps even planted a seed of doubt within those frozen "
"elven hearts, that perhaps their hatred was unwarranted and that there could "
"be a better way."
msgstr ""
"Dans la Forêt Verte, à l'ombre des arbres, la bataille à trois se termina "
"par la fin des vampires, leur Duc Pourpre mort comme s'il avait été percé "
"par la lumière, celle-là même qu'il avait tenté de dissiper. Tout ce qu'il "
"restait de lui un corps au sol, plus que de la nourriture pour des vers de "
"terre.\n"
"\n"
"Maintenant les elfes faisaient face à d'autres ennemis car, bien que peu "
"respirent encore qui avaient vécu leur exil, leur haine des humains était "
"encore profonde.\n"
"\n"
"Cependant, ce jour n'était pas le jour de la revanche car les humains "
"partirent aussi vite que possible, ne voyant pas de raison de combattre une "
"bataille inutile.\n"
"\n"
"En ce jour, les Chevaliers de la Tour d'Argent évitèrent un combat contre "
"d'autres êtres vivants et plantèrent peut-être même le germe d'un doute dans "
"ces cœurs glacés d'elfes, que peut-être cette haine était sans fondement et "
"qu'il existait une autre voie, une meilleure voie."

#. [part]
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\10_Epilogue.cfg:74
msgid ""
"In the darkness a ray of pure light surged forth, piercing through the "
"vampire's heart and breaking his fell artifact.\n"
"        \n"
"As the fell being crumpled, impaled upon a silvery lance, a single ray of "
"sunlight shone upon him as his foul spell broke before the dawn erupted in "
"all its blazing glory, reclaiming its place in the order of things.\n"
"\n"
"And so disappeared the last leader of the vampires much like his liege did "
"the night before, as if to confirm their dark dream's final death and the "
"return of peace to the realm."
msgstr ""
"Des ténèbres un rayon de pure lumière surgit, perçant le cœur du vampire et "
"brisant son maléfique artéfact.\n"
"\n"
"Alors que l'infâme monstre tombait, empalé sur une lance d'argent, un unique "
"rayon de soleil brilla sur lui, brisant son sombre sort et libérant l'aube "
"dans toute son ardente gloire alors qu'elle reprenait sa place dans le "
"monde.\n"
"\n"
"Ainsi disparut le dernier chef des vampires tout comme son seigneur la nuit "
"d'avant, tout comme la mort finale de leur sinistre rêve et le retour de la "
"paix dans le royaume."

#. [part]
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\10_Epilogue.cfg:89
msgid ""
"Before the walls of Dorest a great clash had ended. The duel between the "
"knight and the vampire was over with the would-be conqueror struck down by "
"righteous fury, his hordes run down and exterminated.\n"
"                        \n"
"His death brought relief to every soul, for the North was now freed from a "
"grave threat.\n"
"\n"
"The victorious defenders were celebrated for their courage and the Knights "
"of the Silver Spire above all, for all had seen their valor upon the field "
"of battle."
msgstr ""
"Devant les murs de Dorest un grand combat se finit. Le duel entre le "
"chevalier et le vampire était fini avec l'aspirant conquérant détruit par "
"une fureur vertueuse, ses hordes passées à l'épée et exterminées.\n"
"\n"
"Sa mort apporta un soulagement à chaque âme, car le Nord était maintenant "
"libéré de cette grave menace.\n"
"\n"
"Les victorieux défenseurs furent célébrés pour leur courage, avec les "
"Chevaliers de la Tour d'Argent au premier plan car tous avaient contemplé "
"leur bravoure sur le champ de bataille."

#. [part]
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\10_Epilogue.cfg:100
msgid ""
"Vaedyr and his knights reported the events that had transpired to the lords "
"in Dorest, the treachery of Duke Myrraent and his true identity as the "
"Crimson Duke, vampire and would-be subjugator of the North.\n"
"            \n"
"They were justly recompensed for their actions and led a life of virtue "
"afterwards, continuing to act much as they had before, protecting whomever "
"they could."
msgstr ""
"Vaedyr et ses chevaliers relatèrent les évènements à la noblesse de Dorest, "
"la trahison du duc Myrraent et sa vraie identité en tant que Duc Pourpre, "
"vampire et aspirant conquérant du Nord.\n"
"\n"
"Ils furent bien récompensés pour leurs actions et menèrent des vies "
"virtueuses, continuant à agir comme avant, protégeant tout ceux qu'ils "
"pouvaient."

#. [part]
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\10_Epilogue.cfg:105
msgid ""
"Lady Ariel and the merfolk enjoyed years of peace after the incident, "
"untroubled by other threats from the surface and enjoying the benefits of "
"their newfound renown in the form of lucrative trade with the humans.\n"
"    \n"
"Vaedyr and his men oft visited their shores, reminiscing of battles past and "
"assisting whenever the merfolk's diviners foresaw danger."
msgstr ""
"Dame Ariel et les ondins profitèrent d'années paisibles après le conflit "
"sans être atteints par d'autres menaces et bénéficiant de le nouveau renom "
"ainsi que du commerce lucratif avec les humains.\n"
"\n"
"Vaedyr et ses hommes visitaient souvent leur rive, se remémorant les "
"batailles passées et portant assistance lorsque les oracles ondins "
"prédisaient des dangers."

#. [part]
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\10_Epilogue.cfg:110
msgid ""
"Through the bravery of the knights of the Silver Spire, the North, and "
"perhaps all of the continent, were saved from the depredations of the "
"vampire menace.\n"
"            \n"
"Though this did not save the land from future turmoil, their deeds were "
"fondly remembered and soon passed into legend and, like all such tales, were "
"embellished over time."
msgstr ""
"Par la bravoure des Chevaliers de la Tour d'Argent le Nord, voire tout le "
"continent, furent sauvés des déprédations de la menace vampire.\n"
"\n"
"Bien que cela ne sauva pas ces terres des prochaines tourmentes, leurs "
"exploits étaient chaudement remémorés et devinrent rapidement une légende, "
"qui, comme n'importe quelle autre histoire, fut embellie au fil du temps."

#. [part]
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\10_Epilogue.cfg:123
msgid ""
"Soon, the songs in taverns and stories around the fireplace had forgotten "
"the part the banished elves had played and this became only a tale of the "
"travails of the knights of the Silver Spire, of their desperate stand on the "
"shore of the Avalynne against the Crimson Duke.\n"
"                    \n"
"It told of how, after they had apparently been slain to a man, a maiden of "
"light arose from the water and cried for their fate, bringing about a true "
"miracle.\n"
"\n"
"For before her now stood the entire order, alive and armed, raring to fight "
"once more."
msgstr ""
"Bientôt, les chansons dans les tavernes et fables autour du feu avaient "
"oublié le rôle des elfes exilés et cette histoire n'en devint qu'une des "
"péripéties des Chevaliers de la Tour d'Argent, de leur résistance désespérée "
"sur les rives de l'Avalynne contre le Duc Pourpre.\n"
"\n"
"Ce récit relatait comment, alors qu'ils avaient été tués jusqu'au dernier, "
"une dame de lumière émergea de l'eau et pleura sur leur sort, causant un "
"miracle.\n"
"\n"
"Car devant elle se tenait l'ordre au complet, vivant et vaillant, prêt au "
"combat à nouveau."

#. [part]
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\10_Epilogue.cfg:137
msgid ""
"Soon, the songs in taverns and stories around the fireplace had forgotten "
"the Bloody Baron's flight and was only a tale of the travails of the knights "
"of the Silver Spire, of their desperate stand on the shore of the Avalynne "
"against the Crimson Duke.\n"
"                        \n"
"It told of how, after they had apparently been slain to a man, a maiden of "
"light arose from the water and cried for their fate, bringing about a true "
"miracle.\n"
"    \n"
"For before her now stood the entire order, alive and armed, raring to fight "
"once more."
msgstr ""
"Bientôt, les chansons dans les tavernes et fables autour du feu avaient "
"oublié la fuite du Baron Sanglant et cette histoire n'en devint qu'une des "
"péripéties des Chevaliers de la Tour d'Argent, de leur résistance désespérée "
"sur les rives de l'Avalynne contre le Duc Pourpre.\n"
"\n"
"Ce récit relatait comment, alors qu'ils avaient été tués jusqu'au dernier, "
"une dame de lumière émergea de l'eau et pleura sur leur sort, causant un "
"miracle.\n"
"\n"
"Car devant elle se tenait l'ordre au complet, vivant et vaillant, prêt au "
"combat à nouveau."

#. [part]
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\10_Epilogue.cfg:152
msgid ""
"Soon, the songs in taverns and stories around the fireplace had forgotten "
"the battles of the merfolk and was only a tale of the travails of the "
"knights of the Silver Spire, of their desperate stand on the shore of the "
"Avalynne against the Crimson Duke.\n"
"                        \n"
"It told of how, after they had been slain to a man, a maiden of light arose "
"from the water and cried for their fate, bringing about a true miracle.\n"
"    \n"
"For before her now stood the entire order, alive and armed, raring to fight "
"once more."
msgstr ""
"Bientôt, les chansons dans les tavernes et fables autour du feu avaient "
"oublié les combats des ondins et cette histoire n'en devint qu'une des "
"péripéties des Chevaliers de la Tour d'Argent, de leur résistance désespérée "
"sur les rives de l'Avalynne contre le Duc Pourpre.\n"
"\n"
"Ce récit relatait comment, alors qu'ils avaient été tués jusqu'au dernier, "
"une dame de lumière émergea de l'eau et pleura sur leur sort, causant un "
"miracle.\n"
"\n"
"Car devant elle se tenait l'ordre au complet, vivant et vaillant, prêt au "
"combat à nouveau."

#. [part]
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\10_Epilogue.cfg:163
msgid ""
"This tale was known all through Wesnoth and oft told when the bandits of "
"Asheviere were pillaging the countryside or when the hordes of Mal-Ravanal "
"were slaughtering all they could find.\n"
"            \n"
"All who listened knew that this band of knights was long gone and could not "
"ride against the dark this time."
msgstr ""
"Cette saga était connue partout dans Wesnoth et souvent racontée lorsque les "
"brigands d'Asheviere pillaient la campagne ou quand les hordes de Mal-"
"Ravanal massacraient tous ceux qu'elles trouvaient.\n"
"\n"
"Tous ceux qui écoutaient savaient que cette bande de chevaliers était morte "
"depuis longtemps et ne pourrait pas chevaucher contre la noirceur cette fois-"
"ci."

#. [part]
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\scenarios\10_Epilogue.cfg:168
msgid ""
"It still gave hope, however, that someone would.\n"
"            \n"
"That some plucky band of heroes. whether it be a lost prince and his mentor "
"or some guards from the frontier. would fight back and end this new threat, "
"bringing back peace to the realm.\n"
"\n"
"And that hope, that dream that all would be well in the end, well... that "
"was already a wonderful legacy."
msgstr ""
"Elle donnait par contre un espoir, l'espoir que quelqu'un le ferait.\n"
"\n"
"Qu'une bande de héros courageux, que ce soit un prince perdu et son mentor "
"ou des gardes de la frontière, riposterait et mettrait fin à cette nouvelle "
"menace, ramenant la paix au royaume.\n"
"\n"
"Et cet espoir, cette croyance que tout finirait bien… c'était déjà un "
"magnifique legs."

#. [unit_type]: id=Grandmaster, race=human
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\units\Grandmaster.cfg:7
msgid "Grand Master"
msgstr "Grand maître"

#. [unit_type]: id=Grandmaster, race=human
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\units\Grandmaster.cfg:23
msgid ""
"Grandmasters are the heads of knightly orders, having shown strength of arms "
"upon the battlefield felling countless threats and a strong will directing "
"their fellow knights. These renowned commanders stand at the front of a "
"righteous charge, inspiring their men to launch another assault when others "
"would have broken already, for the glory of their cause and the hope of a "
"better future."
msgstr ""
"Les grands maîtres sont à la tête d'ordres de chevalerie, ayant fait preuve "
"de force par de nombreux faits d'armes sur le champ de bataille en tuant "
"d'innombrables menaces et d'une volonté d'acier en dirigeant leur "
"chevaliers. Ces commandants renommés se tiennent en première ligne d'une "
"charge vertueuse, inspirant leur hommes pour un autre assaut alors que "
"d'autres auraient déjà brisé, pour la gloire de leur cause et l'espoir d'un "
"meilleur futur."

#. [unit_type]: id=Horse Lord, race=human
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\units\Horse_Lord.cfg:7
msgid "Horse Lord"
msgstr "Seigneur des chevaux"

#. [unit_type]: id=Horse Lord, race=human
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\units\Horse_Lord.cfg:22
msgid ""
"The greatest of the men of the plains, Horse Lords are heads of their houses "
"and are respected by all, friend or foe. Their sword can kill most ordinary "
"enemies, and their morning star crushes those who are left."
msgstr ""
"Comptant parmi les meilleurs des hommes des plaines, les seigneurs des "
"chevaux sont à la tête de leurs clans et respectés de tous, amis comme "
"ennemis. Leur épée peut tuer la plupart des adversaires ordinaires et leur "
"étoile du matin écrase ceux qui restent."

#. [unit_type]: id=Horseman Commander, race=human
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\units\Horseman_Commander.cfg:7
msgid "Horseman Commander"
msgstr "Commandant à cheval"

#. [unit_type]: id=Horseman Commander, race=human
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\units\Horseman_Commander.cfg:28
msgid ""
"Leaders of the border guards, mounted commanders command the garrisons that "
"keep peace in the outermost provinces of Wesnoth. As effective leaders and "
"powerful warriors, these men patrol the countryside and eliminate any and "
"all threats to peace in the frontier villages."
msgstr ""
"Dirigeants des gardes frontaliers, les commandants montés mènent la garnison "
"qui assure la paix dans les provinces les plus reculées de Wesnoth. Guides "
"efficaces et guerriers puissants, ces hommes patrouillent la campagne et "
"éliminent toute menace à la paix dans les villages frontaliers."

#. [unit_type]: id=Junior Commander, race=human
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\units\Junior_Commander.cfg:7
msgid "Junior Commander"
msgstr "Jeune commandant"

#. [unit_type]: id=Junior Commander, race=human
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\units\Junior_Commander.cfg:28
msgid ""
"At scarcely 17 or 18 years of age, squires are not yet full knights, but "
"still have the knowledge and skill to master their mounts whilst in full "
"panoply. Talented squires are sometimes given command of small units in "
"Wesnoth’s army, where they gain experience leading fellow troops and honing "
"their prowess in battle."
msgstr ""
"A environ 17 ou 18 ans, les écuyers ne sont pas des chevaliers à part "
"entière, mais ont acquis un savoir et une maîtrise complète de leur monture. "
"Les écuyers les plus compétents obtiennent parfois le commandement d'une "
"petite unité dans l'armée de Wesnoth, où ils gagnent de l'expérience en "
"menant des troupes et en perfectionnant leurs techniques au combat."

#. [unit_type]: id=Mounted Fighter, race=human
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\units\Mounted_Fighter.cfg:7
msgid "Mounted Fighter"
msgstr "Général monté"

#. [unit_type]: id=Mounted Fighter, race=human
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\units\Mounted_Fighter.cfg:21
msgid ""
"The nobles of the men of the plains are trained with the rest of the "
"horsemen to become great warriors. However, they are also trained in "
"commanding their comrades, and they are the ones that become captains of the "
"armies of the Clans."
msgstr ""
"Ls nobles des plaines sont entraînés avec le reste de leurs cavaliers dans "
"le but de devenir de grands guerriers. Toutefois, ils sont aussi entraînés à "
"commander leurs camarades ; ce sont eux qui deviennent les capitaines des "
"armées des clans."

#. [unit_type]: id=Mounted General, race=human
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\units\Mounted_General.cfg:7
msgid "Mounted General"
msgstr "Combattant monté"

#. [unit_type]: id=Mounted General, race=human
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\units\Mounted_General.cfg:29
msgid ""
"Switching seamlessly between lance and mace, mounted generals boast "
"tremendous skill in individual combat and can hold their own against even "
"the most powerful opposition. They are masters of their mounts, able to "
"cover great distances quickly on their patrols, and have keen eyes for "
"detecting and eliminating all manner of perilous dangers. Their greatest "
"strength, however, lies in their ability to inspire great courage in their "
"men, who fight fearlessly and tenaciously under their command."
msgstr ""
"Passant sans effort de la lance à la masse, les généraux montés se vantent "
"d'une grande habilité au combat individuel et peuvent tenir tête à la plus "
"puissante des oppositions. Ils maîtrisent leur monture, sont capables de "
"couvrir de grandes distances rapidement lors de leur patrouille, et ont "
"l'œil pour détecter et éliminer tout danger périlleux. Leur plus grande "
"force, cependant, repose dans leur capacité d'inspirer du courage aux "
"hommes, qui se battent sans peur et avec ténacité sous leur commandement."

#. [unit_type]: id=Mounted Warrior, race=human
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\units\Mounted_Warrior.cfg:7
msgid "Mounted Warrior"
msgstr "Guerrier monté"

#. [unit_type]: id=Mounted Warrior, race=human
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\units\Mounted_Warrior.cfg:21
msgid ""
"Leaders of the plains, Mounted Warriors are skilled with the use of the "
"sword and the morning star. Riding horses, they are able to move around the "
"battlefield with great speed, and can provide much needed assistance to "
"different fronts."
msgstr ""
"Commandants des plaines, les guerriers montés savent parfaitement utiliser "
"l'épée et l'étoile du matin. Ils se déplacent à cheval à travers le champ de "
"bataille avec célérité et peuvent fournir une assistance salutaire sur "
"plusieurs fronts."

#. [attacks]: id=shock
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\utils\abilities.cfg:10
msgid "shock"
msgstr "choc"

#. [attacks]: id=shock
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\utils\abilities.cfg:11
msgid ""
"When this attack is used on offense, the opponent will retaliate with one "
"less strike than normally, to a minimum of one strike."
msgstr ""
"Lorsque cette attaque est utilisée offensivement, l'adversaire répliquera "
"avec un coup de moins que d'habitude, avec un minimum d'un coup."

#. [attacks]: id=shock
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\utils\abilities.cfg:12
msgid ""
"This unit’s melee attack can overwhelm the defenses of enemies, preventing "
"them from retaliating as effectively."
msgstr ""
"L'attaque de mêlée de cette unité peut surpasser les défenses ennemies, les "
"empêchant de riposter efficacement."

#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\utils\characters.cfg:8
msgid "Vaedyr"
msgstr "Vaedyr"

#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\utils\characters.cfg:39
msgid "Lady Ariel"
msgstr "Dame Ariel"

#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\utils\characters.cfg:58
msgid "Duke Myrraent"
msgstr "Duc Myrraent"

#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\utils\characters.cfg:70
msgid "Crimson Duke"
msgstr "Duc Pourpre"

#. [effect]: type=blade
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\utils\characters.cfg:88
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\utils\characters.cfg:156
msgid "fangs"
msgstr "dents"

#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\utils\characters.cfg:115
msgid "Hidden Figure"
msgstr "Figure mystérieuse"

#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\utils\characters.cfg:126
msgid "Baron Luroc"
msgstr "Baron Luroc"

#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\utils\characters.cfg:137
msgid "Bloody Baron"
msgstr "Baron Sanglant"

#. [message]: speaker=unit
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\utils\deaths.cfg:16
msgid "I-I am sorry everyone... I fear I shall not be able to help anymore..."
msgstr ""
"Je-je suis désolé tout le monde... J'ai bien peur que je ne pourrai pas "
"aider plus..."

#. [message]: speaker=unit
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\utils\deaths.cfg:32
msgid "Nooo... My people needed me..."
msgstr "Nooon… Ils ont besoin de moi..."

#. [objective]: condition=lose
#: knights_of_the_silver_spire\utils\misc.cfg:6
msgid "Death of any loyal or leader unit, whether yours or allied"
msgstr "Mort d'un chef où d'une unité loyale, qu'elle soit vôtre ou alliée"

